**who —** 3DO INTERACTIVE MULTIPLAYER — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown

**what —** The 3DO was a specification, not a single product: Trip Hawkins's company licensed a CD-based design that Panasonic, Goldstar, and others built. An ARM CPU with twin custom video coprocessors made it powerful for 1993 — and a 699-dollar launch price made it a commercial cautionary tale.

**where —** the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The 3DO was a specification, not a single product: Trip Hawkins's company licensed a CD-based design that Panasonic, Goldstar, and others built. An ARM CPU with twin custom video coprocessors made it powerful for 1993 — and a 699-dollar launch price made it a commercial cautionary tale.

